<% content_for :title, "About LocalBaker" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "LocalBaker is a simple shop for home bakers. What it does, what it doesn't, and who it's for." %>

<div class="stack-lg">
  <h1>About LocalBaker</h1>

  <div class="stack">
    <p>
      LocalBaker is a shop for home bakers. Built by a home baker who couldn't find one that fit.
    </p>

    <h2>What it does</h2>
    <p>
      Post a bake. Share a link. Customers claim items. You get a pickup list.
    </p>

    <h2>What it doesn't do</h2>
    <p>
      No inventory system. No app to install. No customer passwords. No tier stuffed with features you won't use.
    </p>

    <h2>Who it's for</h2>
    <p>
      People baking 5–50 loaves a week for neighbors, gym lobbies, office swaps. If you run a commercial bakery with a POS and staff, this is too small for you.
    </p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>
      Customers click your link, pick items, and check out. They get a magic-link email — no password to remember. You see a clear list of orders organized by pickup time.
    </p>

    <h2>What it costs</h2>
    <p>
      Free for up to <%= User::FREE_EVENT_LIMIT %> active events. Pro is $9/month — unlimited active events, delivery zones, and customer/follower emails. <%= link_to "See plans", billing_upgrade_path %>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider">

  <div class="stack">
    <p>Ready to bake?</p>
    <div class="group">
      <%= link_to "Open a shop", new_session_path, class: "button primary" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
